  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National legislative approaches:\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n- Financial institution compliance mandates\n\n3. Key regulatory strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n\n4. Specific enforcement mechanisms:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulations\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Targeted sectors:\n- Banking\n- Real estate\n- Securities markets\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory and legal approaches.",
